The briefing led by Gauteng Premier David Makhura will cover the Comprehensive Health Response, schools opening readiness and the economy. JOHANNESBURG - The Provincial Command Council is giving an update on COVID-19 in Gauteng. The briefing led by Gauteng Premier David Makhura will cover the Comprehensive Health Response, schools opening readiness and the economy. READ: COVID-19 in SA: 237 deaths, 2,488 new infections There have been 8,949 coronavirus related deaths in the province while 380,621 people have recovered from the virus. Gauteng currently has 6,990 active COVID-19 cases.